According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Collaborative Robot Market was valued at USD 1.90 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 2.44 billion in 2026 to USD 23.40 billion by 2034, registering an impressive CAGR of 28.6% during the forecast period.
The market is witnessing remarkable growth as manufacturers across industries increasingly adopt collaborative robots (cobots) to improve productivity, enhance workplace safety, and address persistent labor shortages. Unlike traditional industrial robots, collaborative robots are designed to safely operate alongside human workers, enabling flexible automation for applications such as assembly, machine tending, welding, quality inspection, packaging, and material handling.
